# Replace Laravel Logos in Auth and Dashboard

The public site logo now works from CMS Site Settings.

But make it a little bigger: 3rem to be precise

Next, replace the remaining Laravel logos in:

1. Login/auth screens
2. Admin/dashboard header or sidebar

## Objective

Use the CMS-managed site logo everywhere instead of the default Laravel logo.

## Check These Areas

- Login page
- Register page if present
- Forgot password page
- Reset password page
- Email verification page if present
- Admin dashboard
- Admin sidebar/header
- User/investor dashboard if it still shows Laravel logo

## Files to Inspect

- `resources/views/auth/*`
- `resources/views/components/application-logo.blade.php`
- `resources/views/components/authentication-card-logo.blade.php`
- `resources/views/layouts/*`
- `resources/views/components/layouts/*`
- dashboard/admin shell/layout files
- investor layout files

## Required Behaviour

- If CMS logo exists, show uploaded CMS logo.
- If CMS logo does not exist, show text fallback: `The Lylods Group`.
- No Laravel default logo should remain visible.
- Login screen should use the uploaded logo.
- Dashboard/sidebar/header should use the uploaded logo.
- Logo should be appropriately sized in each context.
- Do not change dashboard layout structure.
- Do not redesign auth screens.
- Do not break investor dashboard.

## Implementation Notes

Use the existing SiteSettingService or SiteSetting model helper.

Do not duplicate logo lookup logic.

If needed, create a reusable Blade partial/component:

`resources/views/components/site-logo.blade.php`

It should accept optional classes/size.

